Pre-Game Insights: Australia will play their seventh match of the 2023 Cricket World Cup on Saturday, November 4 when they take on England at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad.
Australia most recently defeated New Zealand in a thriller in Dharmsala on October 28.
England's World Cup defence has imploded, winning just one match out of six.
The Australian batting lineup has begun to click, particularly with the return of Travis Head to the side.
England have looked below-par in every department thus far, and it is difficult to look past an Australian win in this one.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia and England have faced off on 155 occasions in ODIs, with Australia winning 87 of those matches.
